%N A391015 Greedy odd Egyptian fraction representation of Pi-3.
%C A391015 a(n) is the denominator of the largest odd Egyptian fraction, such that the sum of the Egyptian fractions so far does not exceed Pi-3 = 0.14159265358979.... The sum of 1/a(n) is a greedy representation (greedy because each step bites off as much as possible) of Pi-3, using only odd Egyptian fractions.
%H A391015 David Eppstein, <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~eppstein/numth/egypt/">Egyptian fractions</a>
%H A391015 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/EgyptianFraction.html">Egyptian Fraction</a>
%H A391015 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greedy_algorithm_for_Egyptian_fractions">Greedy algorithm for Egyptian fractions</a>
%H A391015 <a href="/index/Ed#Egypt">Index entries for sequences related to Egyptian fractions</a>
%F A391015 a(n) = 2 * ceiling((1/(Pi-3-Sum_{k=1 to n-1} 1/a(k))-1)/2) + 1
%e A391015 a(3)=5603 because 1/(Pi-3-1/9-1/33) = 5601.858788... and the next odd number is 5603.
%o A391015 (PARI) \p 9999
%o A391015 my(r=Pi-3, a); for(n=1, 10, a=2*ceil((1/r-1)/2)+1; print1(a,", "); r=r-1/a)
